   890→  // Connected will be set to false immediately when a disconnect() is
   891→  // requested, even though the channel might still be alive internally to
   892→  // process queued messages. The three states are distinguished as follows:
   893→  // - disconnect() never requested: channel is not null and connected
   894→  //   is true
   895→  // - disconnect() requested, messages in the queue: channel is not null
   896→  //   and connected is false
